<paragraph id="73745F607507530695EF901F7E71EE6E" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">
<bibRefCitation id="ACE9DF099951C3F45274394317E166C9" author="Schembri, SP" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" pagination="90 - 93" refId="B16" refString="Schembri, SP, 1980. Vespoidea from the Maltese Islands (Hymenoptera Aculeata). Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana 112 (4-6): 90 - 93" title="Vespoidea from the Maltese Islands (Hymenoptera Aculeata)." volume="112" year="1980">Schembri (1980)</bibRefCitation>
recorded this species from three females and a male collected in June and July of 1977 and 1978. It is a common circum-Mediterranean species also found in Northern European countries such as Czech Republic and Slovakia and its range also extends as far east as Central Asia. Individuals are highly variable in colour, some being dark while others possess abundant yellow maculations (
<bibRefCitation id="4A6A880EA1ABC9FD08FB750A8B7FAB4D" author="Gusenleitner, J" journalOrPublisher="Eos Madrid" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" refId="B9" refString="Gusenleitner, J, 1995b. Bestimmungstabellen mittel- und suedeuropaeischer Eumeniden (Vespoidea, Hymenoptera) Teil 3: Die Gattung Antepipona SAUSSURE 1855. Linzer Biologische Beitraege 27/1: 183-189." title="Bestimmungstabellen mittel- und suedeuropaeischer Eumeniden (Vespoidea, Hymenoptera) Teil 3: Die Gattung Antepipona SAUSSURE 1855. Linzer Biologische Beitraege 27 / 1: 183 - 189." year="1995 b">Gusenleitner 1995b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
